snippet: The House passed bills delaying two crucial parts of the new  law, requiring most Americans to have insurance and many employers to offer it, that were to take effect in January.
abstract: House of Representatives passes bills delaying two crucial parts of Pres Obama's health care overhaul that require most Americans to have insurance and many employers to offer it, despite a veto threat from Obama.
lead_paragraph: The House passed bills delaying two crucial parts of the new  law, requiring most Americans to have insurance and many employers to offer it, that were to take effect in January.
